{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 18:40:39.821388", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content=\"You are provided with the following network description and its current state:\\nNetwork Description: An enterprise hierarchical network using FRR OSPF with multiple areas: three core routers form the backbone (area 0) with /31 infrastructure links from 172.16.0.0/16,core1/core2 connect to distribution routers, which in turn bridge to access switches. User hosts are statically addressed in subnets `10.<core>.<dist>.0/24` with their default gateway on the distribution switch and DNS pointed to a central DNS server. A server farm in `10.200.0.0/24` hangs off a dedicated OSPF router (area 0) and hosts one Bind DNS server for the `local` zone plus several Apache web servers published as `web0.local`…`web3.local`, all reachable end-to-end via OSPF.\\nSwitches: switch_access_1_1_1, switch_access_2_1_1\\nHosts: host_1_1_1_1, host_2_1_1_1\\nDns Servers: dns_server\\nWeb Servers: web_server_0, web_server_1, web_server_2, web_server_3\\nRouters (FRRRouting): router_core_1, router_core_2, router_core_3, switch_dist_1_1, switch_dist_2_1, switch_server_access\\nTopology: (router_core_1:eth0, router_core_2:eth0), (router_core_1:eth1, router_core_3:eth0), (router_core_1:eth2, switch_dist_1_1:eth0), (router_core_2:eth1, router_core_3:eth1), (router_core_2:eth2, switch_dist_2_1:eth0), (router_core_3:eth2, switch_server_access:eth5), (switch_access_1_1_1:eth1, host_1_1_1_1:eth0), (switch_access_2_1_1:eth1, host_2_1_1_1:eth0), (switch_dist_1_1:eth1, switch_access_1_1_1:eth0), (switch_dist_2_1:eth1, switch_access_2_1_1:eth0), (dns_server:eth0, switch_server_access:eth0), (web_server_0:eth0, switch_server_access:eth1), (web_server_1:eth0, switch_server_access:eth2), (web_server_2:eth0, switch_server_access:eth3), (web_server_3:eth0, switch_server_access:eth4)\\n\\nYour goal is to analyze the network condition and, if needed, use the available tools.\\nYou need to generate a troubeshooting diagnosis 